Text.Value: You're a fool if you think this lot have any loyalty. They'll turn on you in a second.
Ever at your service.
I actually had a pretty good view of the slaughter.
Blessed by association, let's say. I come to pay proper respect to a new power.
Spend enough time in this place, and you might just start to believe them.
Are you a follower of the Absolute?
Such a pity there were no survivors to tell what truly happened there.
'New face'? We've met before - at the goblin camp.
But look at me preaching, and when I'm only here to serve. Anything to trade, True Soul?
A pity neither of us saw what happened.
Lock eyes with the Zhent and gesture in Thieves' Cant: Discount?
Ah, a new face come to bask in the light of the Absolute. How can I be of service, True Soul?
'The Zhentarim'?
Drop the act. What are you actually doing here?
Careful. That sounds like an accusation.
The guilty ear hears blame in every breath. But you're among friends here, True Soul.
You know, you sound less and less like a true believer with every word.
I'm not the one putting on an act, True Soul.  Though I'd mind how well you mouth your prayers.
For now, I'll settle for getting you what you need. Anything to trade?
Oh, True Soul, I couldn't burden your spirit with such material concerns. But I'm always happy to trade.
*The Zhentarim - a network of merchants and mercenaries known for deep coffers and shallow scruples.*
All who pass through here find their way to the Absolute, one way or another.
Can't say I've ever drawn steel on children. Suppose I'm not True Soul material.
Really? You saw nothing at all?
But what would I know of faith? I cater to more earthly needs. Better we focus on that, hm?
Do you have anything to trade?
Stick to trading, then. Show me your wares.
For another in the business? Don't see why not. We can certainly afford it - business is booming.
...of course! Just before some godless lunatic purged the place of every innocent soul.
An honour, True Soul.
Leave.
Ah, yes. The one who saved us from the infidels in the grove.
I'd bow, but the Zhentarim prefer to look their business partners in the eye.
I would hardly call the goblins there 'innocents'.
Indeed. Can I see your wares?
Trade.
If they failed, it was because their faith was weak.
Ah yes - around the time of Minthara's ill-fated expedition to the grove.
Let's see your wares.
Leave.
Let's see what you have.
I've seen your sigil on cargo at the docks. The Zhentarim have joined the Absolute?
Waukeen's clipped coins, no. Faith is an over-flooded market. Transport, however -
Speak for yourself. I had a pretty good view of the slaughter.
You almost sound concerned for my safety.
Quite a god to bring them all together. And quite a fool who'd draw their ire, hm?
What business do mercenaries have with a cult?
I've seen the docks. The Zhentarim have joined the Absolute?
Oh come now - we're far more than just soldiers for hire. Have a bit more imagination.
More concerned that your business might be bad for my business.
So we did. And it seems we both have a nose for where the real power lies - I've come to pay proper respect.
So don't go kicking the hive while there's still some honey to be had.
These faithful folk need some goods moved into the city. Our ships are obliging - quietly.
Smuggling? I want in.
So the Zhentarim have allied themselves with the Absolute?
Spare me. I saw the docks - the Zhentarim have joined the cult.
You didn't strike me as the bleeding heart type.
You were rather quick to find your faith.
Merchants like any other. Though we tend to see opportunity where others don't.
Look around. All manner of beasties united against the enemies of the Absolute.
These faithful folk don't ask for much - just some cargo moved to the city. But my goodness do they pay generously.
Better to keep that quiet, unless you want another look from the receiving end.
Oh, I'm sure they deserved it. I'm all for people getting what they deserve.
How painful the path is - well, that's up to them.
Nothing worth repeating. Corpses don't much go in for commerce. Here, though?
They were a little more frothing-at-the-mouth than faithful, true enough. Here, though?
You're helping the cult expand for a payout. You're disgusting.

Synopsis: A Zhentarim trader from the goblin camp. Roah will react based on your actions if you've met her, or give a brief summary of the Zhentarim's connection to the Absolute if not.
